Your Orbiting Laboratory

The International Space Station is an unprecedented achievement in global human endeavors to build and utilize a research platform in space. Since 2000, the Space Station has evolved from an outpost into a highly capable microgravity laboratory.

Launch Your Future

Opportunities for NASA’s Pathways internships, a work-study program that serves as a starting point for a career at NASA, and Office of STEM Engagement internships for high school and college-level students to contribute to agency missions, close Aug. 21 and 23, respectively.

Image Of The Day

A Practiced Escape

Teams at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center in Florida practice the Artemis mission emergency escape, or egress, procedures on Friday, Aug. 9, 2024. Simulated flight crew members practice getting out of the emergency egress basket and into the emergency transport vehicle to drive them to safety in the event of an unlikely emergency during launch countdown.

Earth Information Center

For more than 50 years, NASA satellites have provided data on Earth's land, water, air, temperature, and climate. NASA's Earth Information Center allows visitors to see how our planet is changing in six key areas: sea level rise and coastal impacts, health and air quality, wildfires, greenhouse gases, sustainable energy, and agriculture.
